tourBios.carHigh:
Has played on eGolf Tour, NGA Tour and Hopkins Tour.

2014: Finished T103 at the Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament in December.

2013: Had a week of firsts at the News Sentinel Open in mid-August. Monday-qualified into the Knoxville event and made the most of his opportunity, in what was only his third start of the season (and fourth of his career). Made his first Web.com Tour cut following opening rounds of 69-68 at Fox Den CC. Came back with a 5-under 66 Saturday and was tied for sixth through 54 holes. Shot another 66 on Sunday, which included a birdie putt on the 18th hole to put him at 15 under and leader in the clubhouse. Watched as Peter Malnati birdied the 18th hole for the win. The T2 finish with three other players vaulted him from no position on the money list to 103rd...Finished T48 the next week in Omaha, his last start of the year.

2012: Advanced to the final stage of the PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament for the first time and earned conditional status on the Web.com Tour after finishing T130.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Won the Georgia 5A state individual title for two years at Harrison High School in Kennesaw, Ga. In winning his second title, set the state championship scoring record (67-65)...Won two college events at Georgia Tech...Was a two-time All-American...Was the 2012 Byron Nelson Award winner...Graduated with highest honors...Was a member of the United States team at the Palmer Cup in 2012...Made his Web.com Tour debut at the 2011 Nationwide Children's Hospital Invitational. Missed the cut after rounds of 72-73.
tourBios.personal: Favorite golf memory growing up was going to the Masters with his dad and watching Tiger Woods...Is a big Atlanta Braves fan...Enjoys watching Robert Griffin III...Favorite course played is Augusta National...Favorite movie is "Braveheart," and his favorite book is Mere Christianity...Top athlete to watch is Russell Wilson...Likes waffles...Most famous person he has met is Jack Nicklaus at the Masters...Would like to switch places for a day with a jet pilot...Dream foursome would include Jesus Christ, Marcus Luttrell and Tiger Woods...Not many people know he almost redshirted the year he won two college tournaments and was a first-team All American...Every one in his family has a first name that starts with a "J"...First-tee intro song would be "Empty Me" by Chris Sligh...Supports the Matt Dyas Memorial Golf Scholarship Fund. Dyas was a good friend...Favorite quote is "You don't have soul. You have a body and are a soul."...Twitter account is @jwhite_golf.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T2nd in 2013 at the News Sentinel Open Presented by Pilot.
